  "notes": "Corsican. Italo-Romance of Corsica, closely related to Tuscan Italian but with its own innovations and archaic retentions. ~100,000 speakers (declining rapidly under French pressure). Key features: (1) Close to medieval Tuscan. (2) Gorgia (aspiration of voiceless stops) in some areas (Tuscan heritage). (3) French superstrate increasing since 1769 (Ferracci 2007, Marchetti 1989).",
